Following the All Progressives Congress (APC) National Convention held in Abuja on Saturday which produces Abdullahi Adamu, former Governor of Nasarawa State as the new National Chairman of the party, the full list of other ratified candidates for the National Working Committee (NWC) and Zonal Leaders of the party is listed below. It could be recalled that President Muhammadu Buhari picked Adamu as a consensus candidate for the post which make George Akume (Benue State), Tanko Al-Makura (Nasarawa), Abdul’Aziz Yari (Zamfara), Sani Musa (Niger), Saliu Mustapha (Kwara) and Etsu Muhammed (Niger) withdrew from the race. The ratification of Adamu and other members of the new NWC and Zonal Leaders of the party was part of activities at the convention at the Eagles Square in Abuja. An ex-deputy governor of Osun State, Iyiola Omisore, emerged as the party’s National Secretary. Other ratified executives include Ijeoma Arodiogwu (National Vice Chairman, South-East), Victor Giadom (National Vice Chairman, South-South), Senator Abubakar Kyari (Borno State) as the Deputy National Chairman (North), Emma Eneukwu (Enugu State) as the Deputy National Chairman (South), Festus Fuanter (Deputy National Secretary). While Isaac Kekemeke emerged as the National Vice Chairman, South-West, Muhazu Rijau (National Vice Chairman, North-Central), Mustapha Salihu (National Vice Chairman, North-East) and Salihu Lukman (National Vice Chairman, North-West). Other are Ahmed El-Marzuk (National Legal Adviser), Uguru Ofoke (National Treasurer), Bashir Gumel (Financial Secretary), Suleiman Argungu (National Organising Secretary), Abubakar Maikafi (National Auditor), Ibrahim Salawu (Deputy National Legal Adviser), Omorede Osifo (Deputy National Treasurer), Beta Edu (National Woman Leader), Abdullahi Israel (National Youth Leader), Tolu Bankole (Special Persons Leader), F.N Nwosu (National Welfare Secretary) and Felix Morka (National Publicity Secretary).